President Donald J. Trump has announced his intention to nominate Stephen Hahn of Texas as the Commissioner of Food and Drugs at the Department of Health and Human Services. Dr. Hahn is currently the Chief Medical Executive at The University of Texas MD Anderson Cancer Center and specializes in treating lung cancer and sarcoma. He has authored numerous research articles and has a background in radiation oncology.

In addition to this nomination, President Trump also announced his intent to appoint several individuals to key positions in his Administration. Catherine Ann Stevens of Alaska is set to be a Member of the Dwight Eisenhower Memorial Commission, Stuart Chikami of Nevada will be a Member of the Commission for the Conservation and Management of Highly Migratory Fish Stocks in the Western and Central Pacific Ocean, and Lee Greenwood of Tennessee is appointed as a Member of the Board of Trustees of the John F. Kennedy Center for the Performing Arts. Furthermore, several individuals have been appointed as Members of the Board of Visitors to the United States Coast Guard Academy.